286
00:10:07,490 --> 00:10:10,057
Yeah, go ahead.
I'll check him out.

287
00:10:10,143 --> 00:10:12,110
Um, okay. I will be
back as soon as I can.

288
00:10:12,178 --> 00:10:13,778
Just don't go crazy

289
00:10:13,847 --> 00:10:15,727
and go into shock or
bleed out or something...

290
00:10:15,782 --> 00:10:18,316
April, I'm fine.

291
00:10:18,385 --> 00:10:19,625
I'll see you soon.

292
00:10:26,026 --> 00:10:29,427
Please don't be surgical.
Please don't be surgical.

293
00:10:31,581 --> 00:10:33,013
Okay, I'm on it.

294
00:10:33,083 --> 00:10:34,966
Oh, it's surgical.

295
00:10:35,035 --> 00:10:36,596
Hey, there you
are. Oh, no. Me first.

296
00:10:36,620 --> 00:10:38,063
Okay, okay. What have
we got? What have we got?

297
00:10:38,087 --> 00:10:39,649
Yeah, a bike messenger
caught in the blast.

298
00:10:39,673 --> 00:10:40,867
My patient's in a lot of pain.

299
00:10:40,891 --> 00:10:42,801
Everybody's patient's
in a lot of pain.

300
00:10:42,825 --> 00:10:44,487
Yeah, these are all
gonna need surgery.

301
00:10:44,511 --> 00:10:45,944
Page Dr. Garrity.

302
00:10:46,012 --> 00:10:47,528
My plane leaves for...

303
00:10:47,597 --> 00:10:48,847
For TED in four hours.

304
00:10:48,899 --> 00:10:50,531
You're going to TED? Mm-hmm.

305
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:52,651
Lucky. My roommate
went last year.

306
00:10:52,719 --> 00:10:54,196
Did tequila shots
with Bill Gates.

307
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,660
It's a fancy people frat party.

308
00:10:55,689 --> 00:10:57,788
Oh, you'll be singing a
different tune next year

309
00:10:57,858 --> 00:10:59,624
when you're there
with your genome stuff.

310
00:10:59,693 --> 00:11:01,587
Ooh, map my genomes.
That sounds like fun.

311
00:11:01,611 --> 00:11:04,545
It's not a spa
treatment. It's science.

312
00:11:04,614 --> 00:11:05,980
Just like building
new cartilage.

313
00:11:06,066 --> 00:11:08,044
As I say in my
speech... Okay, Callie.

314
00:11:08,068 --> 00:11:10,435
Callie. The patients.

315
00:11:10,504 --> 00:11:11,702
No, you're right.

316
00:11:11,771 --> 00:11:13,066
I should keep it fresh for
the conference anyway.

317
00:11:13,090 --> 00:11:14,233
Excuse me.

318
00:11:23,049 --> 00:11:24,694
Uh, just looking
for a status report

319
00:11:24,718 --> 00:11:25,984
for the patient's kid.

320
00:11:26,053 --> 00:11:28,136
The injury extends
into the aortic arch.

321
00:11:28,204 --> 00:11:30,471
So in order to maintain
head perfusion,

322
00:11:30,540 --> 00:11:32,306
I have to bypass
in two circuits.

323
00:11:32,392 --> 00:11:34,403
I'm just waiting on Russell
for a second opinion.

324
00:11:34,427 --> 00:11:35,938
You had to call
Russell for this?

325
00:11:35,962 --> 00:11:37,011
Not really.

326
00:11:37,097 --> 00:11:39,264
But ever since I
became his boss,

327
00:11:39,332 --> 00:11:40,927
I like to make him
think that he's still mine.

328
00:11:40,951 --> 00:11:42,528
3-0 prolene.

329
00:11:42,552 --> 00:11:45,152
So could I give the
kid a time frame?

330
00:11:45,238 --> 00:11:47,439
Uh, give me an
hour. I'll know better.

331
00:11:47,507 --> 00:11:48,739
Okay.

332
00:11:56,616 --> 00:11:58,450
Dr. Shepherd, where did you get,

333
00:11:58,518 --> 00:12:00,434
"It's a beautiful
day to save lives"?

334
00:12:00,503 --> 00:12:02,469
Is that from a movie?

335
00:12:02,538 --> 00:12:04,155
No, it's not from a movie.

336
00:12:04,224 --> 00:12:05,423
Are you sure?

337
00:12:05,491 --> 00:12:07,575
'Cause sometimes I think
I'm making something up,

338
00:12:07,644 --> 00:12:09,288
and then I'm watching
a detergent commercial,

339
00:12:09,312 --> 00:12:11,056
and I realize, that's
where I got that from.

340
00:12:13,049 --> 00:12:15,194
Brooks, you know how sometimes
people downplay the difficulty of a task

341
00:12:15,218 --> 00:12:16,929
by saying, "It's
not brain surgery"?

342
00:12:16,953 --> 00:12:17,953
Sure.

343
00:12:18,021 --> 00:12:19,221
This is brain surgery.

344
00:12:21,107 --> 00:12:22,107
Right.

345
00:12:22,475 --> 00:12:23,958
Sorry.

346
00:12:24,027 --> 00:12:25,638
What are you doing?

347
00:12:25,662 --> 00:12:27,094
He makes me nervous,

348
00:12:27,164 --> 00:12:28,591
and I just want him to like me.

349
00:12:28,615 --> 00:12:30,176
Clearly not the way to do it.

350
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:31,599
Okay, Ross,

351
00:12:31,668 --> 00:12:33,551
now I have exposed the dura,

352
00:12:33,620 --> 00:12:35,247
so why don't you come
closer and get a better look?

353
00:12:35,271 --> 00:12:36,637
He loves you.

354
00:12:36,706 --> 00:12:38,105
I'd been in 20 surgeries

355
00:12:38,174 --> 00:12:40,436
before he ever invited
me to his side of the table.

356
00:12:40,460 --> 00:12:42,820
It could take a while,
but he'll warm up to you.

357
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:45,330
Oh.

358
00:12:47,184 --> 00:12:49,501
You've got some
fast hands, Brooks.

359
00:12:56,059 --> 00:12:58,259
And the baby's out.

360
00:12:58,327 --> 00:12:59,739
I noticed you haven't
thanked me yet

361
00:12:59,763 --> 00:13:01,963
for catching your
patient's prolapsed cord.

362
00:13:02,032 --> 00:13:03,331
I was on my way to the ER.

363
00:13:03,399 --> 00:13:05,327
Yeah, taking your
own sweet time.

364
00:13:05,351 --> 00:13:06,379
You want to cool it, man?

365
00:13:06,403 --> 00:13:07,880
You're being very
unprofessional.

366
00:13:07,904 --> 00:13:10,016
Okay, let's begin to
explore the abdomen.

367
00:13:13,410 --> 00:13:15,793
Oh, God, Elyse. She's
losing too much blood.

368
00:13:15,862 --> 00:13:17,911
More lap pads. Now!

369
00:13:24,804 --> 00:13:26,420
Burn center is full.

370
00:13:26,489 --> 00:13:27,833
I just closed us to new
patients. What else?

371
00:13:27,857 --> 00:13:29,001
Social services came
for the little boy...

372
00:13:29,025 --> 00:13:30,458
Ethan! No!

373
00:13:30,527 --> 00:13:32,176
Whoa. Whoa. Whoa.
Where you going?

374
00:13:32,244 --> 00:13:33,628
I want to see my parents.

375
00:13:33,696 --> 00:13:35,980
Sorry. He's a runner.
Honey, we need to go.

376
00:13:36,049 --> 00:13:37,960
No, I don't want
to. You need sleep.

377
00:13:37,984 --> 00:13:39,283
No, I'm not going anywhere!

378
00:13:39,352 --> 00:13:41,781
Yes, you are. You're
coming with me. Now come.

379
00:13:41,805 --> 00:13:43,498
No. Look, he's worried
about his parents.

380
00:13:43,522 --> 00:13:45,189
How about we set
you up in a room,

381
00:13:45,242 --> 00:13:46,674
and you can stay with him there?

382
00:13:46,743 --> 00:13:48,220
That's not a permanent solution.

383
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:49,577
I know, but it's for one night.

384
00:13:49,646 --> 00:13:51,779
And then we can
figure out the rest later.

385
00:13:51,847 --> 00:13:53,280
How does that sound?

386
00:13:53,349 --> 00:13:54,548
Yeah? Sound good?

387
00:13:54,617 --> 00:13:55,900
Okay.

388
00:13:57,020 --> 00:13:58,986
Come on. We need to go now.

389
00:14:01,908 --> 00:14:03,208
The baby's dad just arrived.

390
00:14:03,276 --> 00:14:04,525
Myers is bringing him up.

391
00:14:04,594 --> 00:14:06,238
I still don't know what
she sees in that D-bag.

392
00:14:06,262 --> 00:14:07,895
Right? What does
she see in that guy?

393
00:14:07,964 --> 00:14:09,613
He's so handsome

394
00:14:09,682 --> 00:14:10,682
and friendly,

395
00:14:10,733 --> 00:14:12,634
charming, nice.

396
00:14:16,105 --> 00:14:17,605
Vince, this is Dr. Karev.

397
00:14:17,674 --> 00:14:20,407
He's been taking
care of your little girl.

398
00:14:20,476 --> 00:14:23,010
Look at her. She...
She's perfect.

399
00:14:23,078 --> 00:14:25,324
She's doing really well.
And I spoke to Dr. Kepner.

400
00:14:25,348 --> 00:14:27,809
Your wife is still in surgery.
We should have an update soon.

401
00:14:27,833 --> 00:14:29,684
Thank you. Thank you very much.

402
00:14:29,752 --> 00:14:31,352
Your baby's pretty darn cute.

403
00:14:31,421 --> 00:14:32,453
Want to hold her?

404
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:42,813
Also sensitive.

405
00:14:42,882 --> 00:14:45,349
Did I mention he's sensitive?

406
00:14:50,156 --> 00:14:51,617
We went home, but
then his fever got higher.

407
00:14:51,641 --> 00:14:52,881
It doesn't make sense.

408
00:14:52,942 --> 00:14:54,253
Ma'am, we'll be with
you as soon as we can.

409
00:14:54,277 --> 00:14:55,976
We're extremely backed up.

410
00:14:56,045 --> 00:14:57,757
Yeah, I understand everyone's
very sick, but so is my son.

411
00:14:57,781 --> 00:14:59,375
Casey, what's wrong? What
are you doing back here?

412
00:14:59,399 --> 00:15:00,475
This isn't strep.

413
00:15:00,499 --> 00:15:02,345
Whatever you
prescribed him did nothing.

414
00:15:02,369 --> 00:15:04,809
It takes at least 24 hours
for antibiotics to start working.

415
00:15:04,837 --> 00:15:07,650
Yeah, but then he should be
getting better, and he's getting worse.

416
00:15:07,674 --> 00:15:09,635
This isn't strep.
Please just calm down.

417
00:15:09,659 --> 00:15:12,526
Calm down? Calm
down? My son is sick.

418
00:15:12,595 --> 00:15:14,435
He's sick, and you
gave him medicine,

419
00:15:14,463 --> 00:15:15,763
and it's not working.

420
00:15:15,832 --> 00:15:17,409
And now you just
keep dismissing us,

421
00:15:17,433 --> 00:15:19,011
just like all the
other doctors did

422
00:15:19,035 --> 00:15:20,379
at Seattle Pres
and Urgent Care...

423
00:15:20,403 --> 00:15:21,685
Wait. Hang on.

424
00:15:21,754 --> 00:15:24,038
You've been to both of
those places, too, this week?

425
00:15:24,107 --> 00:15:26,285
Yeah, and I'm not gonna let
you push me around like they did.

426
00:15:26,309 --> 00:15:29,238
You either don't care about
my son or you don't believe me.

427
00:15:29,262 --> 00:15:31,622
Either way, you suck,
and I want someone else.

428
00:15:31,681 --> 00:15:33,164
Find me another doctor!

429
00:15:33,232 --> 00:15:35,166
Keep an eye on Rachel's ICP.

430
00:15:35,235 --> 00:15:36,355
Update me with any changes.

431
00:15:36,402 --> 00:15:37,851
Will do. Anything else?

432
00:15:37,920 --> 00:15:40,338
Yes, Brooks, think fast.

433
00:15:40,406 --> 00:15:41,788
Anything else medically?

434
00:15:41,857 --> 00:15:43,474
A neuro exam every two hours.

435
00:15:43,543 --> 00:15:44,925
Contact me immediately

436
00:15:44,994 --> 00:15:46,822
if there's any sign of
herniation or a new hemorrhage.

437
00:15:46,846 --> 00:15:47,846
You got it?

438
00:15:47,914 --> 00:15:48,980
Yes, sir.

439
00:15:49,049 --> 00:15:50,049
Good.

440
00:15:50,116 --> 00:15:51,616
Dr. Shepherd, I'm open.

441
00:15:59,308 --> 00:16:00,608
That was my phone.

442
00:16:03,379 --> 00:16:06,580
I'm sorry you have to
stand there for so long,

443
00:16:06,649 --> 00:16:08,082
dealing with my ass.

444
00:16:08,151 --> 00:16:10,418
Ah, it's fine. I'm
a plastic surgeon.

445
00:16:10,486 --> 00:16:11,769
It's not that big a deal to me.

446
00:16:11,837 --> 00:16:13,282
Actually, can we not
talk while you do that?

447
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:16,073
Sure. I feel for you, dude.

448
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:18,192
But I have seen way worse.

449
00:16:18,261 --> 00:16:20,339
Okay. I'm gonna come back later.

450
00:16:20,363 --> 00:16:21,411
April...

451
00:16:21,480 --> 00:16:22,980
It's cool. I'm just gonna...

452
00:16:23,049 --> 00:16:24,849
I'm gonna leave now. Yep. Now.

453
00:16:25,568 --> 00:16:26,834
Like that.

454
00:16:26,903 --> 00:16:28,636
That was worse.

455
00:16:28,704 --> 00:16:31,005
He's cranky, he's
not sleeping well,

456
00:16:31,074 --> 00:16:32,551
and then he's got
these really chapped lips,

457
00:16:32,575 --> 00:16:34,374
and then today it
was this weird rash.

458
00:16:34,443 --> 00:16:36,327
And how are you doing?

459
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:38,896
Are you getting enough sleep?

460
00:16:38,965 --> 00:16:41,399
No, of course not. I
told you, he's up all night.

461
00:16:41,468 --> 00:16:43,401
And it's just you, no husband,

462
00:16:43,470 --> 00:16:45,014
no boyfriend, or partner?

463
00:16:45,038 --> 00:16:46,186
It's just me.

464
00:16:46,255 --> 00:16:48,556
Well, that's a lot
of pressure on you.

465
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:49,840
Are you a psychiatrist?

466
00:16:49,909 --> 00:16:50,925
Casey,

467
00:16:50,994 --> 00:16:52,443
just listen...

468
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:55,212
Oh, my God. You are.

469
00:16:55,965 --> 00:16:57,214
You think I'm crazy.

470
00:16:57,283 --> 00:16:59,217
You think I skip work

471
00:16:59,285 --> 00:17:01,602
and I drag my kid to
the ER, because it's fun,

472
00:17:01,671 --> 00:17:03,304
because I enjoy this?

473
00:17:03,372 --> 00:17:06,007
My son is sick,
okay? He is sick.

474
00:17:06,075 --> 00:17:07,686
He used to wake me
up every morning at dawn

475
00:17:07,710 --> 00:17:09,410
by jumping on my bed.

476
00:17:09,478 --> 00:17:11,318
Now I can barely get him up.

477
00:17:11,380 --> 00:17:13,213
He does this thing
before school...

478
00:17:13,282 --> 00:17:14,726
I let him run out and
get the newspaper...

479
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:17,534
It's his big-kid
chore. He loves it.

480
00:17:17,603 --> 00:17:18,981
He hasn't done it
in a week and a half.

481
00:17:19,005 --> 00:17:20,771
I show him cartoons,
and he doesn't care.

482
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:22,707
I try to get him to eat...

483
00:17:22,775 --> 00:17:25,287
I mean, I even gave him
potato chips for breakfast once,

484
00:17:25,311 --> 00:17:26,777
and... Nothing.

485
00:17:27,981 --> 00:17:29,230
I know

486
00:17:29,299 --> 00:17:31,632
that I am not a doctor,
but you have to believe me.

487
00:17:31,701 --> 00:17:33,534
You have to. You have to.

488
00:17:33,603 --> 00:17:35,068
Hey. Hey, hey, hey.

489
00:17:35,137 --> 00:17:37,338
I believe you.

490
00:17:37,406 --> 00:17:39,368
We're gonna take
care of your son.

491
00:17:39,392 --> 00:17:40,468
Admit him.

492
00:17:40,492 --> 00:17:41,653
I believe you.

493
00:17:45,064 --> 00:17:47,265
Yes, I alerted security.

494
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,144
Of course. I looked all over.

495
00:17:49,168 --> 00:17:50,284
Where's Ethan?

496
00:17:50,352 --> 00:17:52,270
Hang on. I don't know.

497
00:17:52,338 --> 00:17:53,849
