I came back, he was gone.

498
00:17:53,873 --> 00:17:56,006
When? I told you, he's a runner.

499
00:17:56,075 --> 00:17:57,835
When did you lose him?
About a half-hour ago.

500
00:18:00,330 --> 00:18:01,428
Yeah.

501
00:18:20,699 --> 00:18:22,633
No, Shepherd still hates me.

502
00:18:22,701 --> 00:18:24,679
Now he just makes me do tricks.

503
00:18:24,703 --> 00:18:26,915
It takes more than just
good instincts with Shepherd.

504
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,834
You have to be
prepared, diligent...

505
00:18:28,858 --> 00:18:30,635
Says his star pupil.
I'm his circus act.

506
00:18:30,659 --> 00:18:31,820
Wait. Mom.

507
00:18:31,844 --> 00:18:33,055
Hang on, buddy. Mom.

508
00:18:33,079 --> 00:18:34,861
What are you doing?

509
00:18:34,930 --> 00:18:36,358
Who are you? What...
What are you doing?

510
00:18:36,382 --> 00:18:38,098
Why don't we go outside, okay?

511
00:18:38,167 --> 00:18:40,267
It's me, Mom. Ethan.

512
00:18:40,336 --> 00:18:41,480
It's okay, ma'am. Ethan.

513
00:18:41,504 --> 00:18:42,603
It's your son.

514
00:18:42,672 --> 00:18:44,855
No, it's not. Who
is he? Who is that?

515
00:18:44,923 --> 00:18:46,306
